# Autonomous Full-Stack QA Agent ‚Äî Cursor Rules

> **Purpose:** Enforce tech stack, architecture, and coding discipline for this project.
> **Memory Bank:** Read `.cursor/memory/activeContext.md`, `.cursor/memory/progress.md`, and `.cursor/memory/systemPatterns.md` at session start.
> **Scope:** Implement only what is documented in the Memory Bank. Do not invent features outside spec without updating memory files first.

---

## 1. Tech Stack (Locked)

| Requirement | Value |
|-------------|-------|
| Runtime | Node.js **20+** |
| Modules | **ESM** (`"type": "module"` in package.json) |
| Language | **TypeScript strict mode** |
| Entry | `tsx src/index.ts` |

### Approved Runtime Dependencies
`openai`, `playwright`, `pixelmatch`, `pngjs`, `axios`, `chokidar`, `express`, `zod`, `pino`, `dotenv`

**Do not add dependencies** without updating `.cursor/memory/systemArchitecture.md` and `progress.md`.

---

## 2. Core Principles

### KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid)
- Smallest solution that satisfies the requirement.
- One file = one responsibility per the project structure.
- No premature abstraction or speculative configuration.

### DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)
- Shared types in `src/utils/types.ts`.
- Config in `src/utils/config.ts` only ‚Äî no scattered `process.env` reads.
- Logger in `src/utils/logger.ts` ‚Äî no ad-hoc `console.log`.

### YAGNI
- Phase 2 features (Slack, SQLite, baselines CLI, multi-env, GitHub PR) are **out of scope** until Phase 1 core is complete and documented in `progress.md`.
- **No automatic PR creation** ‚Äî patches are applied locally; humans review and commit changes.

---

## 3. Project Structure (Strict)

```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts                  # CLI entry: run | watch | webhook
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ orchestrator.ts           # Main QA cycle ‚Äî wires all layers
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ screenshot.ts         # Playwright capture
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ figma.ts              # Figma REST API
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pixelDiff.ts          # pixelmatch
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ semanticDiff.ts       # Claude Vision
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ routeParser.ts        # Express route extraction
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ testGenerator.ts      # Claude test generation
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ testRunner.ts         # axios execution
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ patcher/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ bugFixer.ts           # Claude patch generation
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ applyPatch.ts         # Write to disk
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ retryLoop.ts          # Re-test with max N retries
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ trigger/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fileWatcher.ts        # chokidar
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ webhookServer.ts      # Express POST /webhook/ci
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.ts             # zod env validation
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types.ts              # Shared interfaces
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ logger.ts             # pino
```

**Rules:**
- New files MUST land in the correct directory. No `src/shared/` ‚Äî use `src/utils/`.
- Cross-layer imports: `orchestrator` may import all layers; layers must NOT import `orchestrator`.
- `utils/` is imported by any layer; `utils/` must NOT import ui/api/patcher/trigger.

---

## 4. Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- `strict: true` ‚Äî no `any` unless justified with inline comment.
- Explicit return types on all exported functions.
- Prefer `async/await` over raw Promise chains.

### Naming
| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Files | camelCase | `pixelDiff.ts` |
| Functions/vars | camelCase | `captureScreenshot` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `TestCase`, `BugReport` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `PIXEL_THRESHOLD` |

### Error Handling
- Validate env at startup via zod in `config.ts` ‚Äî exit with descriptive message if missing.
- Never swallow errors silently.
- Retry logic lives in `patcher/retryLoop.ts` only.

---

## 5. Critical Implementation Rules

These MUST be implemented exactly as specified:

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Pixel threshold** | 2% mismatch ratio. Below ‚Üí ignore. Above ‚Üí semantic diff + patching. |
| **pixelmatch config** | `threshold: 0.1`, `includeAA: false` |
| **Playwright viewport** | 1440√ó900, `networkidle`, viewport screenshot (not full-page) |
| **axios validateStatus** | `validateStatus: () => true` ‚Äî never throw on 4xx/5xx |
| **axios timeout** | 10 seconds per request |
| **No automatic PRs** | On `'fixed'`, log success only ‚Äî do **not** commit, push, or open PRs |
| **Context enrichment** | Each failed patch appends failed file content to `bug.context` before next Claude call |
| **Claude patch output** | Full corrected file only ‚Äî no diff, no markdown fences, no explanation |
| **Figma node IDs** | Convert URL format `1-23` ‚Üí API format `1:23` |
| **File watcher debounce** | 2 seconds via chokidar |
| **Webhook response** | Return `202 Accepted` immediately; run QA cycle async |

---

## 6. Environment Variables

**Required** at startup (validation fails + exit 1 if missing):

```
OPENROUTER_API_KEY, OPENROUTER_MODEL, ROUTES_DIR
```

**Optional with feature flags** (missing/empty is OK ‚Äî check `hasFigma` / `hasGit` on loaded config):

```
FIGMA_API_TOKEN, FIGMA_FILE_KEY  ‚Üí  config.hasFigma
GITHUB_TOKEN                     ‚Üí  config.hasGit
```

**Optional with defaults:**

```
BASE_APP_URL (default http://localhost:3000), MAX_PATCH_RETRIES (default 3)
```

Never commit `.env`. Never log secrets.

---

## 7. AI Agent Operational Rules

### Session Start
1. Read `.cursor/memory/activeContext.md`
2. Read `.cursor/memory/progress.md`
3. Read `.cursor/memory/systemPatterns.md` before adding files or abstractions
4. Consult `.cursor/memory/systemArchitecture.md` before structural changes

### Before Writing Code
- Confirm task maps to a pending item in `progress.md`
- Implement layer-by-layer: utils ‚Üí ui ‚Üí api ‚Üí patcher ‚Üí trigger ‚Üí orchestrator ‚Üí index

### After Completing Work
- Update `progress.md` and `activeContext.md`
- Do **not** commit unless user explicitly requests

### Forbidden Without Approval
- Adding npm dependencies beyond approved stack
- Modifying target app source outside patcher flow
- Automatic git operations (commit, push, PR creation)

---

